body.description: Strong, comfy & sustainably made. We think everything should feel comfortable about your toilet paper, including the way you feel about your impact on the environment. Quilted Northern Ultra Soft & Strong toilet paper is the perfect blend of sustainability and premium comfort, with two soft layers that flex and hold up, all created using responsible manufacturing practices and wrapped in paper you can recycle from the comfort of your own home. Our products are biodegradable, septic safe, and made with no added inks, dyes or fragrances. Our trees are sourced from well-managed, FSC certified forests and other responsible sources. Additionally, we are on a mission to plant 3 Million Trees from 2020-2022 through our partnership with Arbor Day Foundation, and that’s just the beginning!

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: We’ve planted over 3 million trees in 2020-2022 by planting 2 trees for every 1 tree used through out partnership with The Arbor Day Foundation. Better still, 1 tree is replanted by our suppliers. You expect premium quality from Quilted Northern products. That’s why our sheets are 4X stronger & more durable than the leading value brand of toilet paper when wet. With Quilted Northern Ultra Soft & Strong, you get everything you want in a comfy toilet paper and nothing you don’t – including things like added dyes & fragrances you didn’t ask for. The bottom line for you is enjoying our premium softness & strength. The best part? Getting that level of quality from energy-efficient manufacturing practices that make the best use of our resources.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 26, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good stuff worth every cent
reviews.reviewText: I used to buy only Charmin because there's a few things I've never been willing to go with another brand no matter how much money I could save and toilet paper was at the top of that list. Little by little I'm breaking that habit and this is one thing I gotta say I wish I'd tried years ago. I actually think this toilet paper is better than Charmin. I'm impressed with how thick, durable, soft and long lasting it is. I hate generic toilet paper that is so thin you need an industrial size roll just to take care of a number 1 let alone find yourself alone in some friends bathroom with wondering how on earth you're going to take care of a number 2 without everyone knowing when you either block the toilet because you used an entire roll or because it took you an hour and a half to unroll all the toilet paper you needed. That may sound ridiculous to some people but if that's the case you're likely the friend with the generic toilet paper that people dread seeing. If so the fact you're even reading this says you question the fact that you get gifts wrapped in tissue paper that's thicker than your toilet paper and the fact that so many of those gifts were small brown cardboard tubes says it all.This stuff is actually the beginning of my personal journey to find an acceptable balance between price and performance so I can't say for sure that this is the cheapest but it is cheaper than what I'd used before. As for its quality, I find it to be excellent. It's thick yet long lasting and strong yet soft which is what I look for in something that takes care of a subject some people are too uncomfortable to discuss.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 28, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good toilet paper at a good price
reviews.reviewText: Two and a half years after the pandemic started, it can still be difficult to find certain brands of paper products, like toilet paper, in the stores. We like Northern. It’s not too plush but not too thin. I was able to purchase it at a good price here on Amazon. The only concern I have is that this toilet paper does not break down as well as some of the thin, cheap toilet papers. That means although it leaves your bum happy (assuming a bum can be happy), it can be harder on your plumbing and septic system.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good price and quality
reviews.reviewText: This Northern brand is effective & absorbent and thick (2-ply) & soft. I don’t care much for the purple because it leaves little tiny pieces of itself everywhere - and I do mean everywhere. The blue doesn’t “shed.” I usually use the Presto brand but occasionally get this.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Strong and reliable.
reviews.reviewText: I recently had the pleasure of introducing my bathroom to Quilted Northern Ultra Soft and Strong toilet paper, and boy, oh boy, what a ride it has been! Let me tell you, this lovable roll of fluff is like a superhero when it comes to tackling sticky messes. It's as if it has a secret power to make sticky situations disappear faster than Houdini on roller skates!You see, I've tested this toilet paper in the most challenging scenarios. From greasy sludge to chocolate milk-dripping mishaps, it fearlessly took on the stickiness, leaving no trace behind. It's like having a mini-maid at your fingertips—wipe, and voila! Sticky no more! I almost feel sorry for the sticky messes; they never stood a chance against this TP powerhouse! With this TP, you can also forget about getting “lucky.” It’s so strong, your fingers are not busting through.Now, I must mention the special feature that makes this toilet paper the perfect companion for my septic system. Living on a septic tank means I have to be cautious about what goes down the pipes. But fear not, fellow septic comrades, for Quilted Northern Ultra Soft and Strong is septic-friendly! It knows how to do its business while keeping your pipes and septic system happy. It's like having a plumber-approved sidekick who keeps things flowing smoothly!
